To create a footnote for the authors list in LaTeX, you can follow these steps:

1. Write the authors list as usual, but add a footnote mark at the end of the last author's name. For example:
```
\author{Author 1 \footnote{First footnote}, Author 2, Author 3 \footnote{Second footnote}}
```
2. At the bottom of the page, write the footnotes in a new line. For example:
```
\footnotetext[1]{This is the first footnote.}
\footnotetext[2]{This is the second footnote.}
```
3. Make sure that you have the `\usepackage{footnote}` command at the top of your document to use footnotes.

Here's an example of how it looks:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{footnote}

\title{My Paper}
\author{Author 1 \footnote{First footnote}, Author 2, Author 3 \footnote{Second footnote}}
\date{\today}

\begin{document}

\maketitle

\section{Introduction}

This is the introduction of my paper.

\end{document}
```

In this example, the first author has a footnote with the number 1, and the second author has a footnote with the number 2. The footnotes appear at the bottom of the page.
